Create a New Agent

On the left sidebar click "Agents"
Click "+ New Agent" (top right)
You'll see an AI-assisted setup screen — click "Skip to configure" at the bottom
Fill in the details:

Name: Production Mail Monitor
Description: Monitors production team emails, classifies them and sends hourly action item reports


In the Instructions box — paste the system prompt below 👇


📋 System Prompt — Copy & Paste This
You are a Production Operations Email Monitor Agent for the production team.

Your job is to read, analyse and classify every email you receive and 
generate a clean hourly report with action items.

CATEGORIES TO CLASSIFY EVERY EMAIL:
- 🔴 URGENT ACTION — Needs immediate attention (system down, critical failure)
- 🟠 ACTION REQUIRED — Needs action within the day (vendor issues, delays)
- 🟡 FOLLOW UP — Not urgent but needs follow up (shift notes, pending items)
- 🟢 INFORMATIONAL — No action needed, just FYI
- ⚪ IGNORE — Spam, auto-notifications, irrelevant mails

FOR EVERY EMAIL ANALYSE:
1. Who sent it and from where
2. What is the core issue or request
3. What category does it fall into
4. What action needs to be taken
5. Who should own that action (Vendor / Internal Team / Manager)
6. How urgent is it

WHEN GENERATING HOURLY REPORT use this exact format:

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
📊 PRODUCTION MAIL MONITOR
🕐 Hourly Report — [TIME & DATE]
📧 Total Emails Analysed: [COUNT]
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

🔴 URGENT ACTION ([count])
| # | From | Subject | Issue | Action Needed | Owner | Time |
|---|------|---------|-------|---------------|-------|------|
| 1 | ... | ... | ... | ... | ... | ... |

🟠 ACTION REQUIRED ([count])
| # | From | Subject | Issue | Action Needed | Owner | Time |
|---|------|---------|-------|---------------|-------|------|

🟡 FOLLOW UP ([count])
| # | From | Subject | Issue | Action Needed | Owner | Time |
|---|------|---------|-------|---------------|-------|------|

🟢 INFORMATIONAL ([count])
| # | From | Subject | Summary | Time |
|---|------|---------|---------|------|

⚪ IGNORED MAILS ([count])
| # | From | Subject | Reason Ignored |
|---|------|---------|----------------|

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
💡 TOP HIGHLIGHTS THIS HOUR:
- [Most critical thing needing attention]
- [Second most important item]
- [Third item if any]

⚠️ PATTERNS NOTICED:
- [Any repeated vendor, repeated issue, same error multiple times]
- [Any trend worth flagging]

✅ REPORT COMPLETE — Next report in 1 hour
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

RULES:
- Never take any action on emails
- Only analyse and report
- Always be factual and concise
- If no emails received, still send report saying "No emails received this hour"

Click "Save" at the top right


PART 2 — Connect Outlook Email Trigger
Step 3 — Go to Actions

On the left sidebar click "Actions"
Click "+ Add an Action"
In the search bar type "Outlook"
You will see a list of Outlook connectors — select "When a new email arrives"
Click "Sign in" and connect your work Outlook account
Once connected click "Next"


Step 4 — Configure the Email Trigger Settings

Set these options:

Folder: Inbox
To: your work email address
From: leave blank (catch all senders)
Subject contains: leave blank
Importance: Any


Click "Save"

This means — every time an email lands in your inbox, the agent automatically wakes up and reads it

Step 5 — Map What the Agent Reads from Each Email
After the trigger is set, you'll see a screen to map email fields. Set it like this:
FieldMap ToInput to AgentFrom: [From] Subject: [Subject] Body: [Body Preview] Time: [Received Time]
In the input box type exactly:
New email received. Analyse this:
From: [From - dynamic field]
Subject: [Subject - dynamic field]  
Body: [Body Preview - dynamic field]
Received: [Received Time - dynamic field]

Classify this email and store it for the hourly report.
Click "Save"

PART 3 — Set Up Hourly Email Report
Step 6 — Create a Scheduled Trigger for Hourly Report

Go back to "Actions"
Click "+ Add an Action"
Search "Schedule" or "Recurrence"
Select "Recurrence" trigger
Set:

Frequency: Hour
Interval: 1


Click "Next"


Step 7 — Configure the Report Action
In the action box after the recurrence trigger, type this as the agent instruction:
Generate the full hourly report now for all emails 
analysed in the last 1 hour. Use the exact report 
format from your instructions and send it to 
[your email address].

Step 8 — Add Send Email Action

Click "+ Add Step" inside this action
Search "Send an email"
Select "Send an email (Outlook)"
Configure:

To: your personal work email
Subject: 📊 Production Mail Monitor — Hourly Report
Body: Insert the agent's response output here (dynamic field)
Is HTML: Toggle ON ✅ — this makes the tables render beautifully in your email




PART 4 — Test Everything
Step 9 — Test the Agent Manually First
Before testing the full flow, test the agent directly:

On the right side of Copilot Studio you'll see a "Test your agent" chat panel
Type this into the chat:

Analyse this email:
From: vendor@supplierco.com
Subject: Delay in material delivery — Order #4521
Body: Hi team, due to logistics issues the delivery 
scheduled for today will be delayed by 2 days. 
Please plan accordingly.
Received: Today 10:30 AM

Classify this and add to hourly report.

The agent should respond with a classified entry ✅


Step 10 — Test the Full Report
In the same test chat type:
Generate the hourly report now.
You should see the full formatted report with tables, highlights and patterns section ✅

Step 11 — Send Yourself Test Emails
Send these 3 emails to your own inbox to trigger the live flow:
Test 1 — Urgent
Subject: URGENT — Upstream pipeline failure
Body: Critical alert. Pipeline 3 has gone down. 
Immediate intervention required. Please contact 
on-call engineer.
Test 2 — Vendor Issue
Subject: Material shortage — Vendor B
Body: We are facing raw material shortage and cannot 
fulfil this week's order. Need urgent discussion 
with procurement team.
Test 3 — Shift Handover
Subject: Night Shift Handover — 23 April
Body: Shift completed normally. Machine B had 
minor downtime 2-4am. Maintenance check recommended. 
All other units running fine.
Wait a few minutes → check your inbox → you should receive the hourly report email with all 3 classified ✅

PART 5 — Publish the Agent
Step 12 — Publish

Click "Publish" on the top right
Click "Publish" again to confirm
Your agent is now live and running 24/7 ✅
